modules.description: Tracks and aggregates numerical data from labeled sources, supporting real-time enablement or disablement of metrics. Operates on counters, gauges, and timers, with tag-based indexing for fine-grained control. Used to monitor request latencies, error rates, and resource usage in high-throughput services.

Provides metrics sources that collect system resource usage data, including memory and process statistics. Works with tags and returns structured data containing values like virtual size, resident set size, and runtime. Used to monitor application performance and resource consumption in real-time on Unix-like systems.
